1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:40,640
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP18]

3
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:44,400
But hearts can change,

4
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,799
and minds are hard to gauge.

5
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:47,480
How can you be sure
the one you love

6
00:01:48,239 --> 00:01:49,400
is worth it?

7
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:53,400
I do know
such a person,

8
00:01:54,159 --> 00:01:55,159
if you love her,

9
00:01:55,719 --> 00:01:56,680
she's totally worth it.

10
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,159
Who?

11
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,120
You yourself.

12
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,120
No wonder you looked familiar

13
00:02:18,599 --> 00:02:20,120
the moment you walked in.

14
00:02:20,719 --> 00:02:21,800
So it's true,

15
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,039
a real star!

16
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,039
Cai,

17
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:26,759
the real deal really

18
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,159
hits different from a knockoff.

19
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,599
Hey, don't touch!

20
00:02:29,599 --> 00:02:31,000
What 'real vs knockoff'?

21
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,439
Stay away from my idol!

22
00:02:32,439 --> 00:02:33,719
You back off!

23
00:02:33,719 --> 00:02:34,560
- Hey.
- Shican.
Come on,

24
00:02:35,319 --> 00:02:36,840
we finally got rid of you,

25
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,000
why're you back?

26
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,560
My idol's here,

27
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:40,400
of course I'm back!

28
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,719
Like you'd leave otherwise.

29
00:02:41,719 --> 00:02:42,479
That's true.

30
00:02:42,719 --> 00:02:43,560
I was gonna clean up

31
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:45,000
that mess of a room you live in

32
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:45,919
for business.

33
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:46,919
But dad said
leave it.

34
00:02:47,919 --> 00:02:48,840
Just like

35
00:02:49,479 --> 00:02:50,159
he thought!
My idol's here,

36
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:51,639
cut me some slack, please?
You? Slack?

37
00:02:53,199 --> 00:02:53,719
Shican.

38
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:54,800
You brought a guitar,

39
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:55,840
gonna sing?

40
00:02:56,319 --> 00:02:57,319
Of course not.

41
00:02:57,479 --> 00:02:58,159
No way

42
00:02:58,159 --> 00:02:59,680
I'd show off in front of you.

43
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,719
I just wanna hear you…

44
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:02,680
Is that okay?
- Can you?
- Sure.

45
00:03:05,039 --> 00:03:05,879
Wonderful!

46
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:12,719
But they're still busy.

47
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,639
Come on, time for music!

48
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:16,800
Mr. Xu!

49
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,240
Ms. Ruan, come here!

50
00:03:18,719 --> 00:03:19,479
We'll finish the dishes

51
00:03:19,479 --> 00:03:20,680
and come over.

52
00:03:20,719 --> 00:03:21,360
Alright.

53
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:22,479
Go ahead.
You can start.

54
00:03:23,159 --> 00:03:24,080
- Shican.
- She can hear you.

55
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,240
Alright, I'll start.

56
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,479
Nice!

57
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,280
If you wanna listen, go ahead.

58
00:03:44,719 --> 00:03:45,800
I'll wash.

59
00:03:47,719 --> 00:03:49,319
I'm not the type to duck responsibility.

60
00:03:52,719 --> 00:03:53,919
Then what are you responsible for?

61
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,439
These dishes.

62
00:03:59,479 --> 00:03:59,919
Fine.

63
00:04:18,639 --> 00:04:19,480
He just
showed me

64
00:04:20,199 --> 00:04:21,800
photos of your camping trip.

65
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:25,560
It wasn't

66
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:26,920
just us.

67
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,519
It was a team event.

68
00:04:29,279 --> 00:04:29,959
I know.

69
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,639
I just wanna ask,

70
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,680
when the meteor shower came,

71
00:04:37,199 --> 00:04:38,199
what did you wish for?

72
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,759
The moon looks so full tonight,

73
00:04:43,879 --> 00:04:44,839
and so bright.

74
00:04:45,879 --> 00:04:46,680
Why is that?

75
00:04:50,519 --> 00:04:51,360
A shooting star!

76
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:53,920
Quick, make a wish!

77
00:04:54,279 --> 00:04:55,120
So fast!

78
00:04:55,319 --> 00:04:55,920
I…

79
00:05:11,079 --> 00:05:12,480
Why bring that up?

80
00:05:14,279 --> 00:05:15,480
Just wondering,

81
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:17,120
did your wish come true?

82
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:21,120
It came out of nowhere,

83
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:22,439
I was rushing,

84
00:05:22,879 --> 00:05:24,399
couldn't remember what I wished for.

85
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:25,800
I remember.

86
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,199
You saw it too?

87
00:05:34,199 --> 00:05:34,800
Then…

88
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,360
what did you wish?

89
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:42,279
You won't tell me,

90
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:43,680
still trying to get it out of me?

91
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:47,199
I… really

92
00:05:47,199 --> 00:05:48,519
don't remember!

93
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:49,959
Then neither do I.

94
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:52,680
Huaisong, you're so childish!

95
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:54,839
I'm done washing.
Didn't you just say

96
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,839
you'd take responsibility for the dishes?

97
00:05:56,839 --> 00:05:58,199
And you said you remembered!

98
00:05:59,639 --> 00:06:01,040
Quit teasing me like that.

99
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,560
Wanna go listen to music?

100
00:06:56,279 --> 00:06:58,000
Mr. Xu, why're you up so early?

101
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,120
We're off today,

102
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,319
shouldn't you sleep in?

103
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:02,399
Sounds good, right?

104
00:07:02,399 --> 00:07:03,959
Shican, you're amazing! I mean it!

105
00:07:03,959 --> 00:07:04,639
You… didn't expect
you to be that good too!

106
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,399
- Night.
- Night.
Night, Shican.

107
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:07,800
Bye.

108
00:07:11,319 --> 00:07:13,319
Shican, since you're on break,

109
00:07:13,319 --> 00:07:14,399
you should go enjoy yourself.

110
00:07:14,879 --> 00:07:16,720
How about we hit the market

111
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,079
tomorrow at 7:30?

112
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,800
Sure. See you tomorrow.

113
00:07:24,759 --> 00:07:25,959
See you tomorrow?

114
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:12,759
Morning.
Morning.

115
00:08:13,519 --> 00:08:14,120
Morning.

116
00:08:15,319 --> 00:08:16,000
What a coincidence.

117
00:08:16,959 --> 00:08:17,560
Yeah.

118
00:08:17,959 --> 00:08:19,959
Mr. Xu, heading out?

119
00:08:19,959 --> 00:08:21,279
No work today,

120
00:08:21,399 --> 00:08:22,439
just planning to visit the market.

121
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:23,560
What about you?

122
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,199
We're…

123
00:08:26,279 --> 00:08:27,279
Yeah, we're going too.

124
00:08:27,839 --> 00:08:28,680
Then let's go together.

125
00:08:29,079 --> 00:08:29,600
Sure.

126
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,840
Mr. Xu, your acting's wasted,

127
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:42,000
should've been an actor.

128
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,759
Even you noticed,

129
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,720
think she didn't?

130
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:47,120
What are you doing? Hurry up!

131
00:08:48,039 --> 00:08:48,559
Coming!

132
00:08:51,159 --> 00:08:52,919
It's called implied understanding.

133
00:08:57,039 --> 00:08:58,399
What's that?

134
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:22,000
[Last night was an accident.]

135
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:26,200
Why do I sound like such a jerk?

136
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:29,799
[What happened last night,]

137
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:31,000
[don't read too much into it.]

138
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,759
[What if I'm just overthinking?]

139
00:10:35,159 --> 00:10:36,000
[Maybe he never intended]

140
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,559
[to take it seriously.]

141
00:10:40,399 --> 00:10:42,679
[How do I say this in a way that's]

142
00:10:42,679 --> 00:10:45,000
[both proper and polite?]

143
00:10:58,519 --> 00:10:59,399
Morning.

144
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,240
Mingying.

145
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:24,879
Mingying?

146
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:44,399
She left without saying a word?

147
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,360
Does she think I'm
the kind of guy

148
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,320
who won't take responsibility?

149
00:11:53,279 --> 00:11:54,320
[Thanks for last night.]

150
00:11:54,559 --> 00:11:55,679
[Appreciate it, Mr. Liu.]

151
00:11:56,039 --> 00:11:56,960
[I'll treat you to a meal next time.]

152
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:11,519
Appreciate it, Mr. Liu.

153
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,960
Appreciate it, Mr. Liu?

154
00:12:23,799 --> 00:12:24,679
That's it?

155
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:34,000
There are

156
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,840
a lot of traditional handicrafts here.

157
00:12:36,279 --> 00:12:37,600
Here's the paper-cutting,

158
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:39,440
and further ahead, clay figurines.

159
00:12:40,279 --> 00:12:41,759
The one you posted on your Moments?

160
00:12:42,039 --> 00:12:42,679
Which one?

161
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:48,480
This one.

162
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:50,679
It's pyrography gourds.

163
00:12:50,919 --> 00:12:52,279
The shop's just ahead,
at Master Li's place.

164
00:12:52,799 --> 00:12:53,399
I've been

165
00:12:53,399 --> 00:12:54,600
learning there lately.

166
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,039
I'll take you to see.

167
00:12:56,519 --> 00:12:57,039
Okay.

168
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:58,000
Let's go.

169
00:12:58,519 --> 00:12:59,039
Okay.

170
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:01,480
Mr. Xu, what are you looking at?

171
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:02,879
Nothing.

172
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:04,360
Mr. Xu,

173
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,480
are you blocked,

174
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,600
can't even see her Moments?

175
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:11,639
I've been busy lately,

176
00:13:11,639 --> 00:13:12,600
just haven't seen it.

177
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,720
So you did see

178
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:15,519
her post yesterday?

179
00:13:16,399 --> 00:13:18,120
Of course. That photo she picked

180
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,360
was pretty interesting.

181
00:13:20,559 --> 00:13:21,799
But, she didn't

182
00:13:21,799 --> 00:13:23,240
post anything yesterday.

183
00:13:26,159 --> 00:13:27,720
So many things to talk about?

184
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:28,720
If you wanna chat that much,

185
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:30,200
just add each other and talk later.

186
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,240
- Coming.
- Alright.

187
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:33,519
Mr. Xu,

188
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:36,120
that's called entrapment.

189
00:13:45,759 --> 00:13:46,919
Entrapment.

190
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:54,120
Roasting sweet potatoes, sis?
Yeah.

191
00:13:54,799 --> 00:13:56,000
- I gotta try one.
- It's hot!

192
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,080
Haven't had this in ages.

193
00:13:59,080 --> 00:13:59,759
So craved?

194
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:00,879
Smells amazing.

195
00:14:00,879 --> 00:14:02,720
Then stay.

196
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:04,000
Help me out,

197
00:14:04,279 --> 00:14:05,399
I'll roast you some every day.

198
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,840
Can't. I still have to leave.

199
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:10,120
But I've decided,

200
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,960
when Shican finishes his break,

201
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:12,799
I'm leaving with him.

202
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:13,840
Alright.

203
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:15,159
Go then.

204
00:14:15,679 --> 00:14:16,519
Just do me a favor,

205
00:14:16,519 --> 00:14:18,159
take out the trash

206
00:14:18,159 --> 00:14:18,799
on your way out.

207
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:20,559
At your service.

208
00:14:22,679 --> 00:14:23,679
Where are you going?

209
00:14:38,559 --> 00:14:39,320
So good!

210
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:08,600
Excellent!

211
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:10,279
- Amazing!
- Bravo!

212
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,879
Shican, you've got it!

213
00:15:13,679 --> 00:15:14,159
Shican,

214
00:15:14,759 --> 00:15:16,080
got any new songs?

215
00:15:16,279 --> 00:15:17,200
Sing us one, we wanna
hear something fresh.

216
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:18,919
I see you haven't

217
00:15:18,919 --> 00:15:20,159
dropped anything lately,

218
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:22,240
saving something big?

219
00:15:25,039 --> 00:15:25,600
No.

220
00:15:25,679 --> 00:15:27,679
Haven't written anything new.

221
00:15:43,759 --> 00:15:44,919
Isn't this a new one?

222
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:46,440
Why did he throw it away?

223
00:15:49,399 --> 00:15:50,840
In the second part, it says

224
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:52,080
her name

225
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:53,440
first appeared to me

226
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:55,080
in early summer last year,

227
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:56,559
when Ms. Yang Yinyu

228
00:15:56,639 --> 00:15:57,840
was the president of

229
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:58,679
the Women's Normal University.

230
00:15:59,000 --> 00:15:59,759
What time is it?

231
00:16:00,679 --> 00:16:02,240
It was noted later,

232
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:03,639
she was from Wuxi, Jiangsu,

233
00:16:03,639 --> 00:16:05,000
and in 1924 she served as president

234
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:06,600
of Beijing Women's Normal University.

235
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:07,519
That'll be on the test.

236
00:16:07,639 --> 00:16:08,600
Write it down.

237
00:16:09,919 --> 00:16:10,360
And,

238
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:11,639
any ideas

239
00:16:11,759 --> 00:16:12,879
for the reading for the speech?

240
00:16:16,519 --> 00:16:17,639
Alright, that's it for today.

241
00:16:17,639 --> 00:16:18,279
Class dismissed.

242
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:20,840
Ye,
bring your previous work,

243
00:16:21,759 --> 00:16:22,559
let me take another look.

244
00:16:31,120 --> 00:16:32,879
Yi, got you!

245
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:34,720
Why're you chasing me?

246
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:35,799
You've been

247
00:16:35,799 --> 00:16:36,960
running off after class.

248
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:37,519
Tell me,

249
00:16:38,159 --> 00:16:38,759
are you hiding anything
shady from me?

250
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:42,679
What could I hide?

251
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,080
What's in your bag?

252
00:16:44,399 --> 00:16:45,159
Open it.

253
00:16:45,799 --> 00:16:47,879
Just books.

254
00:16:48,159 --> 00:16:49,399
I don't believe, just open it!

255
00:16:50,039 --> 00:16:50,879
Forget it.

256
00:16:50,879 --> 00:16:51,919
I said open it!

257
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:00,080
Give my money back!

258
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:01,440
Sorry, Miss,

259
00:17:01,799 --> 00:17:04,039
no returns once sold.

260
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:07,079
Then explain this.

261
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:08,759
There are…

262
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:11,000
65 of Li Shican's

263
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,680
signed collab cups here.

264
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:13,759
Why didn't my friend

265
00:17:13,759 --> 00:17:15,119
get a single signed one?

266
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:16,960
Those are

267
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:18,759
hidden items.

268
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:19,920
But the official odds
are 1 in 32.

269
00:17:21,960 --> 00:17:23,200
Then you just got unlucky.

270
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:25,920
Today, you ran into me,

271
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:27,119
so that's your bad luck.

272
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,000
Each one is 39 yuan,

273
00:17:30,359 --> 00:17:30,720
and my friend

274
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:31,759
bought 65 of them,

275
00:17:31,759 --> 00:17:32,160
that is

276
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,319
2,535 yuan in total.

277
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:35,960
By law,

278
00:17:36,079 --> 00:17:37,880
large purchases by minors

279
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:39,240
require guardian consent.

280
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:40,359
Otherwise, the transaction is invalid.

281
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,440
Stop talking nonsense.

282
00:17:43,119 --> 00:17:43,599
Fine.

283
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:45,400
Then I'll
call his parents right now

284
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:47,559
and ask if they approved
this kind of spending.

285
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:49,839
Don't!

286
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,000
Shut it!

287
00:17:51,079 --> 00:17:52,000
I won't let anyone bully you!

288
00:17:52,599 --> 00:17:54,160
Wait, he came here

289
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:55,680
and spent the money willingly!

290
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:58,480
Sir,

291
00:17:58,759 --> 00:18:00,359
this kind of thing

292
00:18:00,359 --> 00:18:01,680
shouldn't be near a school.

293
00:18:02,079 --> 00:18:02,720
People online

294
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:04,000
are already reporting this.

295
00:18:04,079 --> 00:18:04,920
And your "win rate"
is fake too.

296
00:18:06,359 --> 00:18:07,440
If you don't refund now,

297
00:18:08,279 --> 00:18:09,119
I'll call the police.

298
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:10,440
No!

299
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:12,720
I'll refund, alright?

300
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:14,720
I'm just unlucky.

301
00:18:16,599 --> 00:18:17,240
Here you go.

302
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:25,440
Yes!

303
00:18:25,599 --> 00:18:27,119
Yes! Yes!

304
00:18:28,519 --> 00:18:29,480
What are you laughing at?

305
00:18:30,119 --> 00:18:31,319
You're rich and reckless.

306
00:18:33,599 --> 00:18:34,680
I just thought

307
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,480
you did poorly on your exam,

308
00:18:36,799 --> 00:18:37,839
so I bought you

309
00:18:37,839 --> 00:18:39,359
a signed cup from Li Shican

310
00:18:39,839 --> 00:18:41,240
to cheer you up.

311
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:42,599
Who knew

312
00:18:42,599 --> 00:18:43,759
he was tied

313
00:18:43,759 --> 00:18:45,240
to a scam like this?

314
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:48,400
That was a decision made by his company.

315
00:18:52,319 --> 00:18:53,680
Why are you looking at me like that?

316
00:18:54,119 --> 00:18:55,279
I just feel

317
00:18:56,119 --> 00:18:57,720
you're terrible at school,

318
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,880
but you're great with numbers.

319
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:07,359
Not just numbers,

320
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:08,680
you're great at reciting laws too.

321
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:10,799
That's more like it.

322
00:19:11,359 --> 00:19:12,920
Well, I have

323
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:13,960
a great lawyer brother.

324
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:16,839
Cai.

325
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:18,359
Why are you back already?
I thought

326
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:20,000
you'd eat out.

327
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:21,480
Cai, you haven't eaten, right?

328
00:19:21,799 --> 00:19:23,160
Let's just eat together.

329
00:19:23,759 --> 00:19:24,640
No need to worry about us.

330
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:26,000
We'll just grab something quick.

331
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:26,440
You guys
eat here.

332
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:28,160
Come over.

333
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:30,640
There were too many people,

334
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:31,960
so we packed some food back.

335
00:19:32,119 --> 00:19:32,880
Call Shishan over.

336
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:34,079
Cai, join us.
So much food,

337
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:35,960
let's all eat together.

338
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:37,599
Yeah, I was wondering

339
00:19:37,839 --> 00:19:38,519
why you ordered

340
00:19:38,519 --> 00:19:40,359
so much.

341
00:19:40,519 --> 00:19:41,200
Because Mr. Xu and I,

342
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:43,160
our tastes

343
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:45,119
are totally incompatible.

344
00:19:46,079 --> 00:19:47,759
Is that the right way to use it?

345
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:50,039
Then 'nitpicking'

346
00:19:50,319 --> 00:19:51,279
works here, right?

347
00:19:52,559 --> 00:19:53,599
I'll go get Hui.

348
00:19:56,039 --> 00:19:56,480
Cai,

349
00:19:56,599 --> 00:19:57,920
go call Shishan down to eat with us.

350
00:19:58,480 --> 00:19:59,480
He's upstairs

351
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:00,519
playing with his guitar.

352
00:20:01,039 --> 00:20:01,920
He's been at it all morning.

353
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:03,359
Never worked this hard before.

354
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,000
I'll go get him.

355
00:20:31,119 --> 00:20:31,599
Thanks.

356
00:20:42,839 --> 00:20:43,400
Shishan,

357
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,240
did you write

358
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:46,240
that piece yourself?

359
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:47,000
You heard it?
Yeah, I did.

360
00:20:47,839 --> 00:20:48,799
It's not mine.

361
00:20:49,119 --> 00:20:49,720
It was…

362
00:20:53,039 --> 00:20:53,799
written by

363
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,160
a senior of mine.

364
00:20:55,839 --> 00:20:57,000
But he didn't finish it.

365
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:58,519
The song hasn't been released yet.

366
00:20:58,880 --> 00:20:59,799
No wonder.

367
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:00,960
How could I

368
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,079
have missed something this good?

369
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:06,319
You think it's good?

370
00:21:06,599 --> 00:21:07,240
Yeah.

371
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:08,799
Even from

372
00:21:08,799 --> 00:21:10,200
that short snippet,

373
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:12,200
it already

374
00:21:12,359 --> 00:21:13,599
tells a story.

375
00:21:14,119 --> 00:21:15,000
It's amazing.

376
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:17,960
What kind of story?

377
00:21:20,720 --> 00:21:21,559
Let me think…

378
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:24,200
Do you remember
back in college

379
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:25,799
when we put on that musical?

380
00:21:26,319 --> 00:21:27,359
I couldn't

381
00:21:27,359 --> 00:21:28,559
come up

382
00:21:28,559 --> 00:21:29,359
with a script then.
And you

383
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:30,799
played me a song.
Do you remember?

384
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:32,359
Yeah, I do.
You said

385
00:21:33,359 --> 00:21:34,599
it was your muse,

386
00:21:34,880 --> 00:21:36,240
that whenever the intro played,

387
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:36,880
you could already see the story.
Right!

388
00:21:37,799 --> 00:21:38,400
When I just heard…

389
00:21:39,359 --> 00:21:40,839
That's exactly how I felt

390
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,000
when I just heard this.

391
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:43,480
It's amazing!

392
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:44,839
Me too!

393
00:21:45,119 --> 00:21:45,759
You know?

394
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:46,960
This piece

395
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:48,559
actually has many versions,

396
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:50,000
but my senior wasn't satisfied

397
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,000
and discarded them all!

398
00:21:51,279 --> 00:21:52,799
But I think it's great!

399
00:21:52,799 --> 00:21:54,119
Yeah, I agree,

400
00:21:54,319 --> 00:21:55,039
it's really good!

401
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:58,319
You writers

402
00:21:58,759 --> 00:21:59,759
and musicians

403
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,759
actually get along pretty well.

404
00:22:03,359 --> 00:22:04,359
Writing and music

405
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:05,480
are just

406
00:22:05,759 --> 00:22:06,880
different forms of expression.

407
00:22:07,119 --> 00:22:09,759
But when it comes to

408
00:22:09,759 --> 00:22:10,880
conveying emotion and energy,

409
00:22:11,039 --> 00:22:12,000
they're really the same.

410
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:13,039
Exactly!

411
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:15,720
Both are powerful!

412
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:21,720
Law is too.

413
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,200
Yeah, law is powerful too.

414
00:22:36,559 --> 00:22:37,160
It really is.

415
00:22:38,799 --> 00:22:40,039
But it seems like

416
00:22:40,039 --> 00:22:41,119
your vinegar's gone, Mr. Xu.

417
00:22:42,359 --> 00:22:43,039
Mr. Xu,

418
00:22:43,319 --> 00:22:45,079
if you can't reach it,

419
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:46,559
you can have mine.

420
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:50,200
We've got plenty of vinegar,

421
00:22:50,519 --> 00:22:51,359
another bottle's right there.
It's fine.

422
00:23:23,599 --> 00:23:24,359
Shican,

423
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:25,920
sorry to interrupt.
You came at the right time.

424
00:23:26,759 --> 00:23:28,000
I was just about to ask you something.

425
00:23:28,839 --> 00:23:29,400
Really?

426
00:23:30,839 --> 00:23:31,400
Come in.

427
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:36,640
Don't be nervous.

428
00:23:38,559 --> 00:23:39,200
Sorry.

429
00:23:39,599 --> 00:23:40,039
Sit down.

430
00:23:41,359 --> 00:23:41,880
Alright.

431
00:23:53,799 --> 00:23:55,039
You said earlier

432
00:23:55,359 --> 00:23:56,880
this song has a certain "taste."

433
00:23:57,759 --> 00:23:58,400
What kind of taste?

434
00:24:00,160 --> 00:24:01,680
Well…

435
00:24:01,799 --> 00:24:02,839
I wouldn't dare say for sure.

436
00:24:04,519 --> 00:24:05,400
Go ahead.

437
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:08,920
Alright, then.

438
00:24:11,880 --> 00:24:13,039
It feels like…

439
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:15,359
the taste of love.

440
00:24:18,119 --> 00:24:18,799
Of course,

441
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,519
it's not the sweet kind.

442
00:24:22,359 --> 00:24:24,079
It has a hint of bitterness

443
00:24:24,480 --> 00:24:25,960
mixed in with the sweetness.

444
00:24:26,720 --> 00:24:28,960
Like the feeling of waiting.

445
00:24:31,519 --> 00:24:32,519
It really sounds like

446
00:24:32,519 --> 00:24:33,799
a song for confessing feelings.

447
00:24:38,279 --> 00:24:39,599
You think it's

448
00:24:40,119 --> 00:24:41,079
for confessing feelings too?

449
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:46,559
Shican,

450
00:24:48,039 --> 00:24:49,200
I actually came here

451
00:24:50,039 --> 00:24:51,440
to apologize.

452
00:24:54,519 --> 00:24:57,200
When I found your score,

453
00:24:58,200 --> 00:24:59,839
I wanted

454
00:24:59,960 --> 00:25:01,680
to study it quietly.

455
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,960
I didn't expect everyone to hear it.

456
00:25:04,599 --> 00:25:05,759
I'm really sorry.

457
00:25:07,279 --> 00:25:08,359
There's nothing to apologize for.

458
00:25:09,640 --> 00:25:10,480
You did me a favor.

459
00:25:13,640 --> 00:25:15,079
Me? A favor?

460
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:17,279
In a few days,

461
00:25:17,319 --> 00:25:18,359
when I finish the piece,

462
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:19,559
you'll understand.

463
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:27,640
Happy New Year!

464
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:31,720
- Tonight.
- Cheers.

465
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,839
- People will think we're drinking.
- Come on.

466
00:25:33,039 --> 00:25:35,440
Tonight, brought to you
by 'Shen'ao's Li Shican,'

467
00:25:36,319 --> 00:25:38,000
the future Chinese superstar,

468
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:38,640
Li Shishan,
- here's a
- Great!

469
00:25:39,559 --> 00:25:41,079
beautiful song for you!

470
00:25:41,079 --> 00:25:42,039
- How does that sound?
- Yes!

471
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:53,799
Morning, Mr. Xu.
Morning, Cai.

472
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:54,920
Morning.

473
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:30,640
[Mingying, I know you're busy.]

474
00:28:31,160 --> 00:28:31,519
[How about]

475
00:28:31,519 --> 00:28:32,599
[I pick you up after work?]

476
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:34,200
[We can talk]

477
00:28:34,559 --> 00:28:35,519
[on the way.]

478
00:28:36,839 --> 00:28:37,559
[Mingying,]

479
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:39,079
[there's a really
popular restaurant lately.]

480
00:28:39,160 --> 00:28:40,119
[Wanna check it out?]

481
00:28:41,599 --> 00:28:42,200
[Mingying,]

482
00:28:42,759 --> 00:28:44,440
[can we talk face-to-face?]

483
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:46,319
[Mingying,]

484
00:28:46,599 --> 00:28:48,000
[do you have time to meet today?]

485
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:49,839
He really doesn't know

486
00:28:49,839 --> 00:28:51,720
how awkward he's being.

487
00:28:58,720 --> 00:28:59,440
Mr. Liu,

488
00:29:00,319 --> 00:29:02,279
it's not that I don't have time,

489
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:04,119
I just don't need to meet you.

490
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:06,359
I've already paid the legal fees.

491
00:29:06,359 --> 00:29:07,720
And I treated you

492
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:09,160
to that meal last week.

493
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:10,519
[So why]
[should we]

494
00:29:11,359 --> 00:29:12,480
[meet again?]

495
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:22,160
You've been

496
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:23,200
sighing all morning.

497
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:24,160
What's wrong?

498
00:29:26,039 --> 00:29:26,799
Nothing,

499
00:29:28,039 --> 00:29:29,400
thanks for asking, Ms. Zhang.

500
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:33,119
You've been frowning for days.

501
00:29:33,119 --> 00:29:34,839
I could help if you want.

502
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:38,279
All good? Fine, I'll get going.

503
00:29:38,480 --> 00:29:39,119
Ms. Zhang.

504
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:42,759
Come back.

505
00:29:44,640 --> 00:29:45,920
Close the door, please.

506
00:29:51,039 --> 00:29:51,960
Take a seat, Ms. Zhang.

507
00:29:57,599 --> 00:30:00,720
Alright, there is a small matter.

508
00:30:03,720 --> 00:30:04,519
My friend

509
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:06,759
recently…

510
00:30:07,359 --> 00:30:09,599
met a girl.

511
00:30:10,359 --> 00:30:11,240
They kind of…

512
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:15,160
hit it off.

513
00:30:16,799 --> 00:30:18,240
That girl said

514
00:30:18,680 --> 00:30:19,920
she'd treat him to a meal.

515
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:21,519
So he tried

516
00:30:21,519 --> 00:30:22,759
to set a time.

517
00:30:23,359 --> 00:30:24,240
But instead,

518
00:30:24,599 --> 00:30:25,799
she ordered takeout

519
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:27,319
and had it sent to his office.

520
00:30:29,079 --> 00:30:29,680
Well,

521
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:31,000
they didn't even meet in person!

522
00:30:32,319 --> 00:30:33,240
Do you think

523
00:30:34,599 --> 00:30:35,640
this is

524
00:30:36,599 --> 00:30:38,000
what they call

525
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:41,480
a "stone-cold woman"?

526
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:46,440
Good question.

527
00:30:54,480 --> 00:30:55,359
There are

528
00:30:55,359 --> 00:30:56,720
no truly "stone-cold men",

529
00:30:57,759 --> 00:30:58,920
just men who don't care.

530
00:30:59,279 --> 00:30:59,920
Likewise,

531
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:01,079
there are

532
00:31:01,079 --> 00:31:02,839
no truly "stone-cold women",

533
00:31:03,759 --> 00:31:05,559
only women who've built walls

534
00:31:05,559 --> 00:31:07,440
to keep you out.

535
00:31:20,039 --> 00:31:21,000
That's my friend,

536
00:31:21,519 --> 00:31:22,160
not me.

537
00:31:22,359 --> 00:31:24,599
Alright, your friend.

538
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:26,559
If he

539
00:31:26,559 --> 00:31:28,079
runs into this kind of wall,

540
00:31:30,319 --> 00:31:31,480
my advice is:

541
00:31:31,480 --> 00:31:33,079
if he doesn't wanna end up all beat up,

542
00:31:33,480 --> 00:31:34,799
better turn back now.

543
00:31:41,960 --> 00:31:42,519
By the way,

544
00:31:44,759 --> 00:31:45,640
it's almost New Year.

545
00:31:46,039 --> 00:31:47,160
Are Mr. Xu and Mr. Chen

546
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:48,519
done in Shen'ao yet?

547
00:31:52,119 --> 00:31:52,759
Here.

548
00:31:59,400 --> 00:31:59,960
Thanks.

549
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:05,279
[Ms. Zhang asked]

550
00:32:05,279 --> 00:32:06,519
[when you'll be back.]

551
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:07,240
[It's year-end,]

552
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:08,880
[we should all get together.]

553
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:12,920
Got it.

554
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:16,079
We should buy tickets soon.

555
00:32:16,559 --> 00:32:18,000
Many time slots

556
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:18,759
are already sold out.

557
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:21,720
Mr. Xu,

558
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:23,200
we should book our tickets too.

559
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:24,039
Work here

560
00:32:24,039 --> 00:32:25,160
is basically wrapped up,

561
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:26,440
the rest can wait until after the holiday.

562
00:32:27,440 --> 00:32:28,279
Honestly, you might as well

563
00:32:28,920 --> 00:32:30,759
all stay and celebrate the New Year here.

564
00:32:31,079 --> 00:32:31,480
It's not

565
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:32,519
like the city here.

566
00:32:32,519 --> 00:32:34,119
New Year is really lively!

567
00:32:34,359 --> 00:32:35,559
You can even watch molten iron fireworks!

568
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:36,759
Molten iron fireworks?

569
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:39,240
That sounds amazing!

570
00:32:40,799 --> 00:32:42,079
I'd like to stay for New Year too.

571
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:44,759
But my parents

572
00:32:44,759 --> 00:32:45,440
are waiting for me at home.

573
00:32:48,319 --> 00:32:50,880
You're the only child, right?

574
00:32:52,599 --> 00:32:53,640
Yeah, if I don't go back,

575
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:54,759
they'll have
a quiet New Year.

576
00:33:07,640 --> 00:33:08,119
Speak of them,
they just texted me.

577
00:33:09,519 --> 00:33:10,799
Probably asking me to go home.

578
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:13,359
[Yu,]

579
00:33:13,759 --> 00:33:14,640
[your dad and I booked]

580
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:15,759
[a 7-day trip to Hainan.]

581
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:17,519
[We're going there for New Year.]

582
00:33:17,720 --> 00:33:18,200
[Make your own plans]

583
00:33:18,200 --> 00:33:19,400
[for New Year this year.]

584
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:49,559
What's up?
Mr. Xu.

585
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:51,559
